Cinder broker enforcers are circulating fraudulent transit seals in the channel lanes, undermining the legal authority of every valid crossing document issued under Kiess route-dispatch certification. The Kiess postmaster has authorized a body count of ten enforcer eliminations as the minimum action needed to collapse the current fraudulent-seal distribution network before the next transit season's documents are issued.
The cinder broker enforcer network has been reduced below operational capacity and fraudulent seal circulation in the channel lanes has dropped sharply. The Kiess postmaster has reissued a corrected transit authorization batch to all affected convoy operators and forwarded an enforcement action report to the Cinder Gate jurisdiction office. The fraudulent-seal incident will be documented in the next quarterly Kiess registry audit.
